Steps to install and set up SASS

1. Opened PowerShell and navigated to the project directory:
   cd Desktop/alx-intermediate-frontend

2. Created a new directory for SASS setup:
   mkdir 0x03-sass_scss
   cd 0x03-sass_scss

3. Verified that Node.js is installed by running:
   node -v
   npm -v

4. Installed SASS using npm:
   npm install sass -v 3.7.4

5. Confirmed that SASS was installed successfully:
   npx sass --version

6. SASS is now ready to use for compiling .scss files into .css.
